canAddScheduleCheck

boolean canAddScheduleCheck(TAuthToken token,
                            long assetId)
                            throws AuthorizationException,
                                   PersistException,
                                   GatewayException,
                                   ServiceException
Parameters:
token - current auth token
assetId - ID of asset that schedule check would be added to
Returns:
true if the currently logged in admin can add a schedule check to the specified asset, false otherwise. Reasons for not being able to add a schedule check include:
  • the user is not allowed to locate the asset
  • the user or asset already has its maximum number of schedule checks, or of alerts in general
  • this user is unauthorized to add schedule checks
  • this deployment doesn't support schedule checks
Throws:
AuthorizationException - -
PersistException - -
GatewayException - -
ServiceException - -

addRegionChangeAlert

@Deprecated
TRegionChangeAlert addRegionChangeAlert(TAuthToken token,

                                                   long landmarkId,
                                                   int radius,
                                                   TAlertDirection direction,
                                                   boolean notifyParentViaEmail,
                                                   boolean notifyParentViaSMS,
                                                   boolean notifyThirdPartyViaEmail,
                                                   java.lang.String thirdPartyEmail)
                                        throws AuthorizationException,
                                               PersistException,
                                               GatewayException,
                                               OperationException.AlreadyAtMaximum,
                                               OperationException.NotFound,
                                               OperationException.NoDataFound,
                                               OperationException.UnsupportedParameterValue,
                                               ServiceException
Deprecated. 

Creates a region chage alert.

Parameters:
token - a sign-in token for an admin.
assetId - the asset to which the new alert should be associated
landmarkId - the landmark to which the new alert should be associated
radius - the radius of the alert, in meters
direction - the direction of the alert
notifyParentViaEmail - -
notifyParentViaSMS - -
notifyThirdPartyViaEmail - -
thirdPartyEmail - - third party to notify, null if none. Must not be null if notifyThirdPartyViaEmail is set.
Returns:
the newly created alerts
Throws:
AuthorizationException - -
PersistException - -
GatewayException - -
OperationException.AlreadyAtMaximum - -
OperationException.NotFound - if the asset with the specified ID could not be found
OperationException.NoDataFound -
  • with paramName "landmark" if the landmark specified could not be found
OperationException.UnsupportedParameterValue -
  • with paramName "direction" if the specified direction is unsupported for this alert type.
ServiceException - -
